n one day and nothing will happen if it is not used.\n\n--  [site:name] team','','10.0.2'),(8927,_binary '[user:display-name],\n\nThank you for registering at [site:name]. Your application for an account is currently pending approval. Once it has been approved, you will receive another email containing information about how to log in, set your password, and other details.\n\n--  [site:name] team','','10.0.2'),(8928,_binary 'Olivero Medium','','10.0.2'),(8929,_binary 'j  F,  Y','PHP date format','10.0.2'),(8930,_binary 'Block Layout Page','','10.0.2'),(8931,_binary 'Block Layout','','10.0.2'),(8932,_binary 'Blocks are boxes of content rendered into an area, or region, of a web page that can be displayed in regions (such as footer or sidebar) on your page.','','10.0.2'),(8933,_binary 'Any custom or contributed block can be added to a particular region by clicking on a button Place block. A new block can also be created by clicking on Place Block','','10.0.2'),(8934,_binary 'Block Region','','10.0.2'),(8935,_binary 'Assign or change the region of a block by clicking here. A dropdown list with all the regions will appear. You can place one block in multiple regions.','','10.0.2'),(8936,_binary 'By Clicking on \"Configure\" you can go ahead and edit the contents of the block, deal with the visibility settings and even change the placement of where it is on your theme.','','10.0.2'),(8937,_binary 'Custom Block Library','','10.0.2'),(8938,_binary 'The block management screen also has an another tab on the top which is used to add Custom blocks. The name of the tab is \"Custom block library\". This tab ultimately provides a link to add custom blocks.','','10.0.2'),(8939,_binary '@interval hence','','10.0.2'),(8940,_binary '@interval ago','','10.0.2'),(8941,_binary 'admin/reports/dblog/event/{{ wid }}','','10.0.2'),(8942,_binary '{{ message }}','','10.0.2'),(8943,_binary 'admin/content/files/usage/{{ fid }}','','10.0.2'),(8944,_binary '1 place@count places','','10.0.2'),(8945,_binary '1@count','','10.0.2'),(8946,_binary '<p>Choose a language from the list, or choose \"Custom language...\" at the end of the list.</p><p>Click the \"Add language\" button when you are done choosing your language.</p><p>When adding a custom language, you will get an additional form where you can provide the name, code, and direction of the language.</p>','','10.0.2'),(8947,_binary '<p>Now that you have an overview of the \"Add languages\" feature, you can continue by:<ul><li>Adding a language</li><li>Adding a custom language</li><li><a href=\"[site:url]admin/config/regional/language\">Viewing configured languages</a></li></ul></p>','','10.0.2'),(8948,_binary '<p>You cannot change the code of a language on the site, since it is used by the system to keep track of the language.</p>','','10.0.2'),(8949,_binary '<p>The language name is used throughout the site for all users and is written in English. Names of built-in languages can be translated using the Interface Translation module, and names of both built-in and custom languages can be translated using the Configuration Translation module.</p>','','10.0.2'),(8950,_binary '<p>Choose if the language is a \"Left to right\" or \"Right to left\" language.</p><p>Note that not all themes support \"Right to left\" layouts, so test your theme if you are using \"Right to left\".</p>','','10.0.2'),(8951,_binary '<p>Now that you have an overview of the \"Edit language\" feature, you can continue by:<ul><li>Editing a language</li><li><a href=\"[site:url]admin/config/regional/language\">Viewing configured languages</a></li></ul></p>','','10.0.2'),(8952,_binary '<p>To reorder the languages on your site, use the drag icons next to each language.</p><p>The order shown here is the display order for language lists on the site such as in the language switcher blocks provided by the Interface Translation and Content Translation modules.</p><p>When you are done with reordering the languages, click the \"Save configuration\" button for the changes to take effect.</p>','','10.0.2'),(8953,_binary '<p>You can change the default language of the site by choosing one of your configured languages as default. The site will use the default language in situations where no choice is made but a language should be set, for example as the language of the displayed interface.</p>','','10.0.2'),(8954,_binary '<p>Operations are provided for editing and deleting your languages.</p><p>You can edit the name and the direction of the language.</p><p>Deleted languages can be added back at a later time. Deleting a language will remove all interface translations associated with it, and content in this language will be set to be language neutral. Note that you cannot delete the default language of the site.</p>','','10.0.2'),(8955,_binary '<p>Now that you have an overview of the \"Languages\" page, you can continue by:<ul><li><a href=\"[site:url]admin/config/regional/language/add\">Adding a language</a></li><li>Reordering languages</li><li>Editing a language</li><li>Deleting a language</li></ul></p>','','10.0.2'),(8956,_binary 'This page allows you to translate the user interface or modify existing translations. If you have installed your site initially in English, you must first add another language on the <a href=\"[site:url]admin/config/regional/language\">Languages page</a>, in order to use this page.','','10.0.2'),(8957,_binary 'You can write your own translation in the text fields of the right column. Try to figure out in which context the text will be used in order to translate it in the appropriate way.','','10.0.2'),(8958,_binary 'When you have finished your translations, click on the <em>Save translations</em> button. You must save your translations, each time before changing the page or making a new search.','','10.0.2'),(8959,_binary 'The translations you have made here will be used on your site\'s user interface. If you want to use them on another site or modify them on an external translation editor, you can <a href=\"[site:url]admin/config/regional/translate/export\">export them</a> to a .po file and <a href=\"[site:url]admin/config/regional/translate/import\">import them</a> later.','','10.0.2'),(8960,_binary 'Welcome!','','10.0.2'),(8961,_binary 'All content, by letter.','','10.0.2'),(8962,_binary '@interval','','10.0.2'),(8963,_binary 'Search form (narrow)','','10.0.2'),(8964,_binary 'Search form (wide)','','10.0.2'),(8965,_binary '<em>You haven’t created any frontpage content yet.</em>','','10.0.2'),(8966,_binary 'Congratulations and welcome to the Drupal community.','','10.0.2'),(8967,_binary 'Drupal is an open source platform for building amazing digital experiences. It’s made, used, taught, documented, and marketed by the <a href=\"@drupal_community\">Drupal community</a>. Our community is made up of people from around the world with a shared set of <a href=\"@drupal_values\">values</a>, collaborating together in a respectful manner. As we like to say:','','10.0.2'),(8968,_binary 'Come for the code, stay for the community.','','10.0.2'),(8969,_binary 'Get Started','','10.0.2'),(8970,_binary 'There are a few ways to get started with Drupal:','','10.0.2'),(8971,_binary '<a href=\"@drupal_user_guide\">User Guide:</a> Includes installing, administering, site building, and maintaining the content of a Drupal website.','','10.0.2'),(8972,_binary '<a href=\"@create_content\">Create Content:</a> Want to get right to work? Start adding content. <strong>Note:</strong> the information on this page will go away once you add content to your site. Read on and bookmark resources of interest.','','10.0.2'),(8973,_binary '<a href=\"@drupal_extend\">Extend Drupal:</a> Drupal’s core software can be extended and customized in remarkable ways. Install additional functionality and change the look of your site using addons contributed by our community.','','10.0.2'),(8974,_binary 'Next Steps','','10.0.2'),(8975,_binary 'Bookmark these links to our active Drupal community groups and support resources.','','10.0.2'),(8976,_binary '<a href=\"@drupal_global_training_days\">Global Training Days:</a> Helpful information for evaluating Drupal as a framework and as a career path. Taught in your local language.','','10.0.2'),(8977,_binary '<a href=\"@drupal_events\">Upcoming Events:</a> Learn and connect with others at conferences and events held around the world.','','10.0.2'),(8978,_binary '<a href=\"@drupal_community\">Community Page:</a> List of key Drupal community groups with their own content.','','10.0.2'),(8979,_binary 'Get support and chat with the Drupal community on <a href=\"@drupal_slack\">Slack</a> or <a href=\"@drupal_chat\">DrupalChat</a>. When you’re looking for a solution to a problem, go to <a href=\"@drupal_answers\">Drupal Answers on Stack Exchange</a>.','','10.0.2'),(8980,_binary 'Configuration synchronization','','10.0.7'),(8981,_binary 'Configure languages for content, interface, and configuration.','','10.0.7'),(8982,_binary 'Sticky header','','10.0.7'),(8983,_binary 'Main Menu','','10.0.7'),(8984,_binary 'Search by keyword or phrase.','','10.0.7'),(8985,_binary 'Search Form','','10.0.7'),(8986,_binary 'Powered by','','10.0.7'),(8987,_binary 'Drupal Logo','','10.0.7'),(8988,_binary 'Filter the contents of the %view_title view','','10.0.2'),(8989,_binary 'Tabs display toggle','','10.0.7'),(8990,_binary 'Authored on','','10.0.2'),(8991,_binary 'Text alternative','','10.0.2'),(8992,_binary 'Decorative image','','10.0.2'),(8993,_binary 'Add missing alternative text','','10.0.2'),(8994,_binary 'Change image alternative text','','10.0.2'),(8995,_binary 'Drupal core security coverage','','10.0.7'),(8996,_binary 'Database Isolation Level','','10.0.7'),(8997,_binary 'PHP APCu caching','','10.0.7'),(8998,_binary 'Database support for JSON','','10.0.7'),(8999,_binary 'Checked','Examined','10.0.7'),(9000,_binary 'エラーエラー','','10.0.7'),(9001,_binary 'CheckedChecked','','10.0.7'),(9002,_binary 'Status Details','','10.0.7'),(9003,_binary 'For the best performance and to minimize locking issues, the READ-COMMITTED transaction isolation level is recommended. See the <a href=\":performance_doc\">setting MySQL transaction isolation level</a> page for more information.','','10.0.7'),(9004,_binary 'Is required in Drupal 10.0.','','10.0.7'),(9005,_binary 'Covered until @end_version','','10.0.7'),(9006,_binary 'Visit the <a href=\":url\">release cycle overview</a> for more information on supported releases.','','10.0.7'),(9007,_binary 'Supported image file format: %formats.Supported image file formats: %formats.','','10.0.7'),(9008,_binary 'PHP APCu caching can improve your site\'s performance considerably. It is <strong>highly recommended</strong> to have <a href=\"https://www.php.net/manual/apcu.installation.php\" target=\"_blank\">APCu</a> installed on your server.','','10.0.7'),(9009,_binary 'For more detailed information, see the <a href=\"https://www.drupal.org/docs/updating-drupal\">Updating Drupal guide</a>. If you are unsure what these terms mean you should probably contact your hosting provider.','','10.0.7'),(9010,_binary 'Post updating @extension','','10.0.7');
